# Phase Backwards Compatibility (mandatory)

Every phase must **not break** prior phase deliverables. Full standard: [`docs/agent/standards/common/backwards-compatibility.md`](../../docs/agent/standards/common/backwards-compatibility.md).

## Hard requirements

- **API**: Additive changes only at `/api/v1/*`; `GET /api/health` and `GET /api/v1/me` (Phase 1) must keep working.
- **Tests**: New phase tests + update `test/e2e/phase1-backwards-compat.e2e-spec.ts` (or phase-specific compat suite).
- **Demos**: `scripts/phase{N}-demo.sh` must include Phase 1 health smoke; `docs/demo/phase{N}-demo.md` must cover Postman + frontend inspection.
- **OpenAPI**: `bun run api:validate` must pass before phase sign-off.

## STOP if

- A prior-phase endpoint returns unexpected status or shape without approved deprecation.
- Phase demo script passes but Phase 1 smoke fails.
- Postman Phase 1 requests break.
